column7: description
May this helmet fend off the mighty dances of those you dare face...
It flew like a feather and as an axe slew. Like music, it awoke my body, my soul, my brain.
Sometimes standing still, wallowing in the water, can be a much wiser move than going forward.
You may spend your life seeking the emerald ring... and it would be a life well spent.
Love is fickle, shifting, urgent. But it is only painful if something within you is in pain.
This powerful pendant has brought balance and harmony to the lawless Nomads for centuries.
This ancient shield cointains the power of all the warriors who've used it.
Befriend the creatures of death. They know it best.
Fickle fox finds frail freedom for his friends to keep safe. Will you fight or will you flake?
They say gold is only glitz, but gold is concrete. It's tangible. I say glory is glitz— only gold matters.
They told me to trust God, but I couldn't find him. So I trusted my chainmail instead.
...but the crossbow taught me that distance can too be an ally in the deadly dance of life.
True demons are never within. True demons are those who take you over, who make be someone else.
The sand forged a shield that compressed its very soul, a shield could be the vast desert.
Fancy yourself strong as the mighty dragon, evasive as fire...
They say glory is a sad word and I agree... Like sadness, glory requires every fiber of your soul.
Iron withstands the stroke of the sword. Gold resists the merciless lightning.
But I never truly felt the Rhythm Queen without my golden ring...
Stakes are higher in a battle when your demons are involved.
Let your hands be as fast as a lightning; only then you can say you dance.
They forged an axe of mithril, and its unfaltering beauty seemed meaningless next to its eternal strength.
All looks jolly as Christmas draws closer, but worry not my dear! Evil's just around the corner.
Royalty is not something I was born with, but a cloak I learnt to wear.
The scythe first reaped harvests... now it reaps victories.
A brave arm makes a short sword long.
Let silk hold your body like a coccoon long enough for your wings to grow.
Get a dog and you'll always have a friend on the road. That's why I prefer spiders.
Dark and cluttered like the nest where it lay, the spider ring will make you invincible... or eat you slowly inside.
The spike tunic kept Saladin safe from his greatest weakness: self doubt.
This ring used to be the belt of Fatso de Dwarf. And if it held its belly, it could hold anything.
Those who fear protect their heads... and those who dance protect their hearts.
Choose Aki like you choose a friend: blindly, inexplicably. Sometimes a mask can be the truest of friends.
Guardian angels are not in the sky, gladiator... they're in your head.
Earth teaches us to dance. Sky teaches us to fly.
Assassins don't actually need protection. They need lightness to sway away from death.
No one knew shine could be black until this meteor-crafted sword blinded us with its darkness.
An armour made of the blue of the moon at its highest, when everything is silent, everything is possible...
The blue scimitar called me, and its cold steel seemed to say: a true mage can also use the earthly blade.
Ah, Captain, the stories this armor can't tell...
Slay like you're not yourself, like you are the dark music that runs through your veins.
Dragons spit fire because they hold life in every breath... and so does this shield.
El Yelmo, the Spanish called it, and the beauty of its name rang within me like an everlasting battle.
Never underestimate the power of sight: once your target's been spotted, you have only a choice to make.
Fire is untouchable because it's forever shifting. It burns like urgency, like an untamed desire.
It is only to a true warrior that the golden falchion reveals itself.
And the lives of those unfairly killed forever lived in this shield, ready for revenge..
Learn from the hooded bandits: trick the sand into letting you through, scam the heat into giving way.
A katana will only obey a man who can dance. May this katana be the arm you lack.
But the crown did not just give me power... it gave me the will to call this wretched world mine.
Yes, gladiator. This hat —magic itself, if you will— is but an illusion. But then again, what isn't?
Wands are not made. It's the wood that chooses to become one. It's the wood that allows itself to be used.
This ring will not reveal its powers instantly: it'll take time to master them, like catching a lighting bolt with your bare eye.
Poison is slow but incredibly deadly. This dagger wins battles like a man works the land: slowly, steadily, mercilessly.
Deception is simply the tiny slit of a dagger into the fabric of truth.
Will I, Queen of Rhythm, forfeit my royal pendant to any but the best?
Bear this spear like a symbol to what royalty truly is: the power of all mankind rolled into one man.
From our own ruins we shall rise again.
Legend has it this ring showed Saladin his way back when he lost himself.
Sometimes temptation can be the road to self-knowledge.
And out of nowere, the spears started flying like bolts of lightning, like music...
Wear the spike armor and you need only wait. All your opponent's attacks will simply bounce back.
Wear this pendant and learn not to control wind, but to sway to its mighty rhythm.
Feed this scimitar blood and its blade will keep sharp.
You do not take in darkness; darkness takes you in. Black magic is nothing but  untamed magic.
Killing a dragon is like defying nature. It's going against gravity, it's controlling fire.
Only then I realized: death does not mean to stop living. Death means to stop fighting.
You can cast the fireball, gladiator, but beware: great power usually entails great recoil.
Cold can make your heart numb. And there's nothing more painful than dancing with a numb heart.
These robes have seen demons, sacrifice. They've seen blood curl out of a living body like a mighty snake.
Being a samurai means breathing in the silence, mastering the stillness of your mind...
Then I saw it: true desire sometimes comes from our darkest, and oftentimes it hides in our fears.
The Vindicator was forged with such heavy magic that its weilding became impossible but for the strongest paladins.
And Uka lead me to the deaf vibrations of darkness and, for once, I allowed myself to follow.
It's the tiniest creatures that know the biggest secrets of your way...
Claw your way to enlightment, tear silence into music and music into silence.
The dagger, a simple weapon, will not show you its power, but present you with yours.
The giant shield will certainly protect you, gladiator, if only you bear to look small.
Defense is merely the reforging of your opponent's offence...
The royal guard has served the colosseum for decades. No one will teach you to fight in it like them.
From the mud the axe rose, and slowly thumped away my fears...
Pound your feet, pound your hammer. It's not your mind but your body that'll keep you alert.
Fear can be a fertile soil, but a true sultan will keep its buds at bay.
Know yourself, gladiator, and the most basic material will do to protect those you hold most dearly...
